                            <comment id="17140658" author="asbachb" created="Fri, 19 Jun 2020 16:01:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This creates the folder during logger initialization: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/blob/log4j-2.13.3/log4j-core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/appender/rolling/AbstractRolloverStrategy.java#L111-L117&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/blob/log4j-2.13.3/log4j-core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/appender/rolling/AbstractRolloverStrategy.java#L111-L117&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17140662" author="asbachb" created="Fri, 19 Jun 2020 16:11:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rgoers&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rgoers&quot;&gt;rgoers&lt;/a&gt; I wonder which component should create that folder name in this case. The RolloverStrategy or the FileAppender itself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17140697" author="asbachb" created="Fri, 19 Jun 2020 17:06:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I changed &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/blob/log4j-2.13.3/log4j-core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/appender/rolling/AbstractRolloverStrategy.java#L93&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/blob/log4j-2.13.3/log4j-core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/appender/rolling/AbstractRolloverStrategy.java#L93&lt;/a&gt; to&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
manager.getPatternProcessor().formatFileName(strSubstitutor, buf, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;, NotANumber.NAN);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which seems to work. Unsure if there&apos;s any drawback.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17150135" author="asbachb" created="Thu, 2 Jul 2020 09:45:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rgoers&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rgoers&quot;&gt;rgoers&lt;/a&gt; any thoughts about that patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17167490" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Wed, 29 Jul 2020 20:25:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am not sure why changing useCurrentTime from false to true would cause a directory to be created. I will incorporate your unit test into the build and see what I can determine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
